# Model Governance Rules

- Prioritize safety over confidence: support abstain/defer paths for low-certainty predictions.
- Include bias checks across relevant cohorts; document fairness metrics and known limitations.
- Add deviation detection: data drift, concept drift, and prediction distribution shift monitoring.
- Track quality metrics continuously (accuracy/F1 where relevant, calibration, false-positive/false-negative tradeoffs, latency).
- Version datasets, model artifacts, prompts/configs, and evaluation baselines for reproducibility.
- Never train/evaluate on leaked targets, contaminated splits, or untraceable data sources.
- Log model decisions in a privacy-safe way for auditability and incident review.